  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Food Security and Livelihoods Restoration in Sindh Province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Affected population(s)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of agriculture inputs and tools through voucher shemes. Training of farmers on integrated crop management. Provision of cash for work opportunities. Provision of cash grants for setting up micro-enterprises.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is part of the ACT Alliance&apos;s Appeal Pak 102 that was launched as flood response to the disaster affected communities of Pakistan. The Appeal targets both emergency needs and early recovery needs of the flood affected communities in target districts.  As part of early recovery, one of the components was restoration of livelihood to ensure food security of flood affected communities in Khaipur and Swat districts. Under this component, the communities were provided with: vouchers to obtain agriculture inputs; cash for work opportunities to rehabilitate their livelihood and rural infrastructure; and cash grants to set-up their micro-enterprises.</narrative>
  </description>
